[thinking] **Exploring automatic derivation**
[thinking] 
[thinking] I’m considering the implications of missing tuple functionality in Circe's automatic derivation for sealed trait families. It looks like existing semiautomatic and automatic products address sealed traits, but I’m wondering about adding auto for sealed traits, which might not yet exist. I'll test the derivation for sealed traits without explicit instances, ensuring not to duplicate logic flows already present. There’s also the possibility of including case objects since Scala 3 handles them differently.
[thinking] 
[thinking] **Evaluating automatic derivation**
[thinking] 
[thinking] I’m noting that there’s no need to re-test cases already covered. When comparing case objects to enum singletons, they might have similarities. It seems that "automatic derivation supports sealed trait families without explicit instances" is a better focus, possibly including nested products, although I might worry about duplication. I also need to test for decoders that fill in missing fields, so I’ll check if that functionality is supported by the generic implementations. It’s time to inspect the core derivation sources for clarity!
[thinking] 
